at0000.1.description: Series of questions and associated answers used to screen for the administration of vaccination.

at0027.1.description: Is there a history of administration of any vaccinations related to the screening purpose?
at0027.1.comment: In a template, the data element would usually be renamed to the specific question asked. The proposed value set can be adapted for local use by using the DV_TEXT or the DV_BOOLEAN datatypes choice to match each specific use case.

at0024.1.description: Is there a history of use of a specific vaccine or group of vaccines.
at0024.1.comment:
In a template, the data element would usually be renamed to the specific question asked. The proposed value set can be adapted for local use by using the DV_TEXT or the DV_BOOLEAN datatypes choice to match each specific use case. 
For example an alternative valueset using the DV_TEXT datatype can be: 
Currently using [The individual currently uses the specific medication either on a regular basis or as required.]
Never used [The individual has never used the specific medication.]
Used in the past [The individual has used the specific medication in the past, but isn't currently using it.]
Unknown [It is not known whether the individual uses or has used the specific medication.]

at0026.1.description: Details about a specified vaccine or grouping of vaccines relevant for the screening purpose.
at0026.1.comment: Use separate instances of this CLUSTER to differentiate between specific medications or groupings of medication.

at0015.1.description: The date or partial date when the individual first started frequent or regular, but usually non-daily, smoking of tobacco of any type.
at0015.1.comment: Can be a partial date, for example, only a year. For example, this date could represent when the individual commenced smoking every Friday night or at parties.

at0023.1.description: Estimate of number of units of the specified type of tobacco consumed.
at0023.1.comment: For example: the number of 'sticks' or 'full pipes' per day or per week. This data element is redundant if a value is recorded for 'Typical use(mass)'.

at0000.1.description: Series of questions and associated answers used to screen for issues, problems or diagnoses.

at0040.1.description: Timing of the initial recognition of the issue, problem or diagnosis.
at0040.1.comment:
The 'Onset' data element is deliberately loosely modelled to support the myriad of ways that it can be used in questionnaires to capture the onset of a problem or the timing of a diagnosis. The specific and intended semantics can be further clarified in a template. 

For example:
Date/time for the date of diagnosis. Interval of date/time for a period of time eg. between 1940 and 1942. Text for descriptions like 'Immediately after the operation', or 'Up to one week ago', 'Up to two weeks ago', 'Three weeks ago'. Duration for the individual's age at the onset. Interval of Duration for the approximate age of the individual at the time of onset.
